profitable growth that will be focused in the areas of expanded offerings and services, including acquisitions. In 2018, we
acquired ECM S.p.A. and Downer Freight Rail. Each quarter, our Board of Directors reviews the company's dividend for the
applicable quarter. The Board evaluates the financial condition of the company and considers the economic outlook, corporate
cash flow, the company's liquidity needs, and the health and stability of global credit markets to determine whether to maintain
or change the quarterly dividend. Dividends paid totaled $1.95 billion in 2018, representing 78 cents per share paid in the first
and second quarter, and 86 cents per share paid in the third quarter and fourth quarter. In January 2014, the Board of Directors
